OK, I am fairly confident that commit 1541ce56cf2d fixed the issue in main (notice the `s/inactive/failed/` change in the test). 4.4.1-rhel does _not_ have this commit (see https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/v4.4.1-rhel/test/system/250-systemd.bats#L429-L441), so the test will flake there unless we file a BZ and backport.

As mentioned above, the "slightly different symptom" is the the EBUSY fart (see https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/17216) preventing container cleanup.

@edsantiago feel free to double check. The `Error: no pod with name or ID test_pod found: no such pod` are red herrings that popped up when cleaning up the systemd service after the test failure.
